This paper deals with network function virtualization (NFV) and software-defined networking (SDN) in the context of fifth-generation (5G) networks. It focuses on multicast service orchestration and joint traffic routing and virtual network function (NF) placement. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with optimization problems, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, it involves mathematical programming, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
